  "summary": "# Weekly Market Briefing \u2014 Week Ending May 31, 2026\n\n## 1. Market Overview\nBroad indices posted a solidly positive week, led by tech-heavy QQQ (+2.89%) outpacing SPY (+1.45%), VTI (+1.57%), and DIA (+0.92%). Small caps (IWM +1.86%) also participated, suggesting reasonably broad risk appetite. The Nasdaq-S&P spread (~144 bps) signals a clear growth/tech leadership rotation. Notably, bonds rallied alongside equities (TLT +1.28%, BND +0.63%), and gold edged up (+0.80%) \u2014 an unusual \"everything rally\" excluding energy and defensives.\n\n## 2. Sector Performance\n**Outperformers:**\n- **XLK Technology (+5.89%)** \u2014 the standout, driven by semis and software earnings momentum.\n- **XLB Materials (+1.71%)** and **XLY Consumer Discretionary (+1.42%)** \u2014 cyclically constructive.\n\n**Underperformers:**\n- **XLE Energy (-5.38%)** \u2014 sharp decline on heavy volume (41.7M), pointing to a crude price reset.\n- **XLP Staples (-2.23%)**, **XLU Utilities (-2.05%)**, **XLRE Real Estate (-1.28%)** \u2014 classic defensive/yield rotation OUT as risk assets bid.\n- **XLF Financials (-0.69%)** and **XLV Healthcare (-0.28%)** \u2014 modestly weaker.\n\nThe pattern is a clean risk-on rotation: investors abandoned defensives and energy in favor of growth/tech.\n\n## 3. Notable Movers\n- **SNOW +48.40%** on heavy volume (19.1M) \u2014 the week's largest move, likely earnings-driven.\n- **PLTR +14.36%** and **SHOP +15.25%** \u2014 high-beta growth surge.\n- **AMD +10.39%** and **AVGO +7.88%** \u2014 semiconductor strength; **MSFT +7.57%** and **CRM +6.13%** reinforce enterprise software bid.\n- **NVDA -1.95%** on outsized volume (191M) \u2014 notable divergence from semi peers.\n- **XOM -6.24%** and **CVX -4.69%** \u2014 confirming the energy slide.\n- **JNJ -3.29%, PEP -4.24%, KO -3.03%** \u2014 dividend defensives broadly weaker.\n- Crypto was quietly negative (BTC -1.04%, ETH -0.67%), diverging from equity risk-on tone.\n\n## 4. Key Metrics\n- **Valuation watch:** TSLA P/E 399.8, AMD 172.6, PLTR 175.9, SHOP 116.4, AVGO 86.9 \u2014 froth concentrated in momentum names. XLK P/E at 41.9 is elevated vs. SPY at 28.4.\n- **Encouraging:** Financials (XLF P/E 16.6) and Communication Services (XLC 17.0) remain reasonably valued. Bond rally lowers discount-rate pressure on growth multiples.\n- **Divergence flag:** NVDA underperforming while AMD/AVGO surge is unusual \u2014 worth monitoring for rotation within semis.\n- **Volume signal:** XLE's 41.7M volume on a -5.38% week suggests capitulation-style selling in energy.\n\n## 5. Themes to Watch\n1. **Tech leadership sustainability** \u2014 Can XLK extend gains, or does the SNOW/PLTR/SHOP melt-up signal late-stage euphoria?\n2. **Energy reset** \u2014 Watch crude fundamentals; XOM/CVX selloff on heavy volume needs context (OPEC, demand data).\n3. **Defensive rotation** \u2014 Staples, utilities, REITs all down suggests low recession fear; reversal would signal sentiment shift.\n4. **Rates & bonds** \u2014 TLT strength alongside equities is notable; if yields keep falling, growth multiples get further support.\n5. **Crypto divergence** \u2014 Risk-on equities + risk-off crypto is unusual; monitor BTC's hold above $73K.\n6. **NVDA vs. semi peers** \u2014 Watch for sector-internal rotation signals.",
